A resident living in an old age home in Langa in Cape Town has been killed in a fire that broke out. CAPE TOWN A resident living in an old age home in Langa in Cape Town has been killed in a fire that broke out earlier this afternoon.The cause of the blaze is unknown at this stage but firefighters have worked to extinguish the flames that forced residents to be evacuated from the area.Rescue services Theo Layne said, One male adult sustained fatal wounds and one female sustained injuries and was taken to hospital. 